Eleco up after director share buying . Shares in building materials group Eleco Holdings Plc jumped 17 percent on Tuesday after a press report highlighted recent director share purchases , dealers said . As London trading resumed after Monday ' s public holiday , the stock was up 3 - 1 / 2p at 23 - 3 / 4 by 0906 GMT in volume of 325 , 909 shares . The Sunday Times said Eleco chairman John Ketteley had recently increased his stake in the group and other directors had also bought shares in recent months . The paper said an upturn in the housing market should boost the company ' s results this year , after it reported a pre - tax loss of 96 , 000 stg in the six months to December 1996 . - - David Holmes , London Newsroom + 44 171 542 4367 
